{"image_id": "UNM_2006_page_78", "image_size": [1275, 1650], "ocr": [{"text": "60", "bbox": [627.0, 1554.8, 653.2, 1575.6]}, {"text": "transfer, persistency for fully insured group short-term income protection was slightly higher than expected for", "bbox": [150.0, 153.6, 1079.1, 174.5]}, {"text": "2005.  It was anticipated that persistency in the group income protection business would decline in 2005 due to our", "bbox": [150.0, 177.6, 1113.3, 198.4]}, {"text": "more disciplined approach to pricing, renewals, and risk selection.  Since the group life and accidental death and", "bbox": [150.0, 201.5, 1092.4, 222.4]}, {"text": "dismemberment products are generally sold in conjunction with group income protection, the more focused renewal", "bbox": [150.0, 225.5, 1122.0, 246.3]}, {"text": "effort in group income protection reduced persistency in these lines, though the reduction in persistency was less", "bbox": [150.0, 249.5, 1094.2, 270.3]}, {"text": "than anticipated.  The persistency for the supplemental and voluntary product lines generally continued to be within", "bbox": [150.0, 273.4, 1119.6, 294.2]}, {"text": "expected levels.", "bbox": [150.0, 297.4, 288.2, 318.2]}, {"text": "Unum US Group Income Protection Operating Results", "bbox": [150.0, 345.0, 612.2, 365.9]}, {"text": "Shown below are financial results and key performance indicators for Unum US group income protection.", "bbox": [150.0, 393.2, 1039.8, 414.1]}, {"text": "(in millions of dollars, except ratios)", "bbox": [154.3, 441.9, 432.3, 460.8]}, {"text": "2006", "bbox": [633.3, 488.9, 671.4, 507.8]}, {"text": "% Change", "bbox": [721.1, 488.9, 798.9, 507.8]}, {"text": "2005", "bbox": [844.8, 488.9, 882.9, 507.8]}, {"text": "% Change", "bbox": [928.7, 488.9, 1006.5, 507.8]}, {"text": "2004", "bbox": [1052.4, 488.9, 1090.6, 507.8]}, {"text": "Operating Revenue", "bbox": [154.3, 511.9, 311.7, 530.8]}, {"text": "Premium Income", "bbox": [154.3, 535.7, 298.5, 554.6]}, {"text": "Group Long-term Income Pr